way (P4) is experimentally validated and scores very highly (0.93). (2) The network topology is rich with 23 molecules, 15 reactions, 4 well-connected hubs (HCN, NH\u2083, H\u2082S, formate), and 4 convergence points. (3) Environmental flow from Hydrothermal (feedstock generation) \u2192 Surface (cyanosulfidic chemistry) \u2192 Biochemical (peptide assembly) is clearly established and well-justified. (4) The catalytic H\u2082S and NH\u2083 recycling cycles are correctly captured. (5) Two independent HCN sources (formamide decomposition and atmospheric photochemistry) provide convergent feedstock supply. (6) Literature alignment is outstanding \u2014 the network directly implements the Patel et al. pathway with correct intermediates, agents, and conditions. Minor weaknesses: (a) rxn_002 (formate \u2192 formaldehyde) has limited experimental support. (b) Some Surface reactions (rxn_005, rxn_008) lack explicit mineral catalyst specification. (c) rxn_007 is mislabeled as Surface when it is atmospheric photochemistry. (d) Glycine is introduced in rxn_015 without being synthesized within the network. (e) The network correctly notes the racemic product but could more explicitly address the chirality question. Overall, this network demonstrates sophisticated understanding of prebiotic chemistry, strong literature grounding, and sound network design principles.\",\n  \"approved\": true,\n  \"hub_quality\": 0.93,\n  \"convergence_quality\": 0.90\n}", "parsed_response": {"pathway_evaluations": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_001": 0.88, "rxn_002": 0.72, "rxn_003": 0.85, "rxn_004": 0.78, "rxn_005": 0.75, "rxn_006": 0.88, "rxn_008": 0.78, "rxn_009": 0.82, "rxn_010": 0.93, "rxn_011": 0.93, "rxn_012": 0.9, "rxn_013": 0.93, "rxn_014": 0.9}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.84, "pathway_coherence": 0.88, "environmental_progression": 0.9, "target_achievement": 0.95, "overall_confidence": 0.89, "feedback": "Comprehensive 13-step pathway tracing CO\u2082 all the way to DL-Proli